{{Infobox medical condition (new) | name = Trigonitis | image = | caption = | | pronounce = | field = | synonyms = | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }} {{refimprove|date=December 2011}} '''Trigonitis''' is a condition of [[inflammation]] of the [[Trigone of urinary bladder|trigone region]] of the [[urinary bladder|bladder]]. It is more common in women.
The cause of trigonitis is not known, and there is no solid treatment. [[Electrocautery]] is sometimes used, but is generally unreliable as a treatment, and typically does not have quick results. Several drugs, such as [[muscle relaxants]], [[antibiotics]], [[antiseptics]] such as [[Urised]], have varied and unreliable results. Other forms of treatment include [[urethrotomy]], [[cryosurgery]], and [[neurostimulation]]. ==References== {{Reflist}} == External links == {{Medical resources | DiseasesDB = | ICD10 = {{ICD10|N|30|3|n|30}} | ICD9 = {{ICD9|595.3}} | ICDO = | OMIM = | MedlinePlus = | eMedicineSubj = med | eMedicineTopic = 2343 | MeshID = }} * [http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/416644_4 Medscape Link]
